{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"846ad16e-b1d9-43b6-84cf-b9e8c3f189b0","agentId":"aaea9d56f23028c83","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"Read the file /app/tools/run_cbmc.py (and any helper it imports under /app/tools/util/) and report EXACTLY how it invokes CBMC for verifying a single function's contracts. I specifically need:\n\n1. The exact `goto-cc` command/args (does it compile in stub files from /app/stubs/? always or conditionally?).\n2. The exact `goto-instrument` command/args — especially: does it pass `--malloc-may-fail` or `--no-malloc-may-fail`? What `--unwind` and `--partial-loops` settings? Does it use `--replace-call-with-contract` and `--enforce-contract`?\n3. The exact `cbmc` command/args — especially `--depth`, `--malloc-may-fail` / `--no-malloc-may-fail`, `--object-bits`, `--unwind`, or any other flags.\n4. Whether/when it adds the /app/stubs/cprover_alloc.c file to the compilation.\n\nQuote the relevant code lines verbatim (with line numbers). Do not summarize loosely — I need the precise flag strings. If there are constants or lists of flags defined, quote them."},"uuid":"c67a9378-a4e2-4807-811b-8cef32d8cafc","timestamp":"2026-06-27T03:08:54.426Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"sdk-cli","cwd":"/app","sessionId":"0afa13b1-f6b8-4c02-acfb-825b0bd267f3","version":"2.1.191","gitBranch":"treatments/minus-tools"}
